    "The only exception is that the S-CNN and FC models were specifically designed to pass the soil data measured at the soil surface directly to the LSTM cells.",
    "Although the soil data is generally static, the subscript of soil data in Figure 2 allows the possibility of changing soil conditions over time.",
    "The use of historical average yield data as part of the input allows the RNN model to predict crop yield using historical trend of crop yield even without weather or soil data.",
    "Suppose year t is the target year of yield prediction, then in the test phase, the average yield in year t, Ŷ t, can be substituted with Y t-1, and the unobserved portion of weather data in W t can be substituted with the predicted weather data.",
